  "body": "## Environment:\n\n<!-- Please complete the following information, when reporting bugs related to the IceCubesApp. -->\n\n - OS: Mac OS 26.1\n <!-- [e.g. iOS vX.Y.Z] -->\n - IceCubesApp version: 2.1.0\n <!-- [e.g. IceCubesApp vX.Y.Z] -->\n\n## Description\n\n### This does not work\nWhen I choose a remote local timeline from the sidebar and then try to change to view local/federated/trending, nothing happens at all\n\n<img width=\"993\" height=\"808\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ec52fbb1-219e-428f-821d-36693399a04e\" />\n\n### This DOES work\nHowever, if from my timeline view I choose the same remote local timeline from the top bar menu, it works fine and I am able to choose from this menu\n\n<img width=\"893\" height=\"802\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1e12011f-b5d7-446f-86c1-f886fe2434b2\" />\n\n<img width=\"989\" height=\"812\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f1783d61-d23d-4b5a-8a86-d83c185fb648\" />\n\n## Related Issues\n\n - [x] Search that this bugs don't already exist before creating it.\n \n<!-- Are there any existing issues or pull requests related to this problem? If so, link them here. -->",
